# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 
    ==> Quick view: a web application that wants to redirect a user to a new page inserts this header into the 
                    HTTP response.

    ==> attack scenario example: unauthenticated  user will be redirect to http response including the following header
        location:http://www.elsfoo.com/login, the user's browser will analyze the header of the HTTP response and will
        perform a new GET request to the new page (login) without showing the content body of the first request.
        but the content body will shown during intercepting of HTTP response that could be has sensitive information.
# ------------------------------- start overview ------------------------------- # 